04:09:21','2012-03-09 04:09:21','',103,'http://spiraldesign.ca/wp-content/uploads/2012/03/Interview-David-Gensler-21.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(127,1,'2012-03-09 04:09:51','2012-03-09 04:09:51','','Interview-David-Gensler','','inherit','open','open','','interview-david-gensler-4','','','2012-03-09 04:09:51','2012-03-09 04:09:51','',102,'http://spiraldesign.ca/wp-content/uploads/2012/03/Interview-David-Gensler1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(128,1,'2012-03-09 04:40:27','2012-03-09 04:40:27','<div><img class=\"right\" src=\"http://spiraldesign.ca/wp-content/uploads/2012/03/interview-image-1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"325\" height=\"434\" /></div>\n<h3 class=\"question\">Asher:</h3>\nWhere did you grow up?\n<h3 class=\"answer\">David:</h3>\nI was born in Baltimore, Maryland. I lived there until I was in the 4th grade, then moved to Berks County, Pennsylvania. I have lived in California several times in my life, Colorado, Philadelphia and now call Brooklyn, New York home.\n<h3 class=\"question\">Asher:</h3>\nHow did you first get into design and business?\n<h3 class=\"answer\">David:</h3>\nI was always more interested in what was behind the scenes, than what was on the surface. This curiosity to discover has lead me down an alternative and rewarding road. I started my formal education in Photography, then shifted to Industrial Design and Advertising. My affinity for writing opened doors for me in business and strategy, which lead me back to business school to focus on marketing and strategy.\nYou put all those things together and you have a wide array of tools to help you build and manage brands. Most recently I have once again shifted to intense studies in digital strategy and before that fashion design. Always stay in a constant state of learning and growing - otherwise you will lose your competitive edge.\n<blockquote class=\"right\">“I was always more interested in what was behind the scenes, than what was on the surface.”</blockquote>\n<h3 class=\"question\">Asher:</h3>\nWho are your day to day partners at The KDU and SVSV and what are their specific rolls?\n<h3 class=\"answer\">David:</h3>\nI have some amazing people who surround me and make things happen. Jared Liner is my Creative Director and day to day studio manger partner. He holds the studio together in regards to projects and clients. My wife, Margarita also handles operations and is who I feel most comfortable putting in front of press and sales for SVSV. Josh Vanover, while not based in Brooklyn is a partner who leads the “art” side of the army. His work is pushing the cutting edge right now and brings me the most inspiration.\n<div><img class=\"left\" src=\"http://spiraldesign.ca/wp-content/uploads/2012/03/interview-image-2.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></div>\n<h3 class=\"question\">Asher:</h3>\nYou have so many things going on at the moment, what are the most recent developments of SVSV?\n<h3 class=\"answer\">David:</h3>\nWe are be working hard to expand our in-house factory. We named the factory, Brooklyn Sewn and it has been an amazing and rewarding experience. We are also trying to get back to our roots with more avant garde work to balance the more contemporary work we have been producing lately - the trick is finding the balance between both worlds.\n<h3 class=\"question\">Asher:</h3>\nThe KDU is growing daily with new designers, can you tell us about them?\n<h3 class=\"answer\">David:</h3>\nEach designer, artists or creative professional is hand selected by me personally. People are recommended from other members and colleagues, but the ultimate selection process is determined by me alone. I want the KDU to continue to stand in opposition to mass, technology driven platform and crowd sourcing collectives - the only way to truly avoid this is to know each member personally, having an intimate understanding of their portfolios, work styles and flow.','Oliver Cartwright','','inherit','open','open','','104-autosave','','','2012-03-09 04:40:27','2012-03-09 04:40:27','',104,'http://spiraldesign.ca/104-autosave/',0,'revision','',0),(129,1,'2012-03-10 23:12:29','2012-03-10 23:12:29','','Interview-David-Gensler','','inherit','open','open','','interview-david-gensler-5','','','2012-03-10 23:12:29','2012-03-10 23:12:29','',72,'http://spiraldesign.ca/wp-content/uploads/2012/03/Interview-David-Gensler2.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(130,1,'2012-03-10 23:20:05','2012-03-10 23:20:05','','Interview Custom Fields','','inherit','open','open','','acf_interview-custom-fields-11','','','2012-03-10 23:20:05','2012-03-10 23:20:05','',31,'http://spiraldesign.ca/acf_interview-custom-fields-11/',0,'revision','',0),(133,1,'2012-03-11 00:19:28','2012-03-11 00:19:28','','Interview Custom Fields','','inherit','open','open','','acf_interview-custom-fields-14','','','2012-03-11 00:19:28','2012-03-11 00:19:28','',31,'http://spiraldesign.ca/acf_interview-custom-fields-14/',0,'revision','',0),(134,1,'2012-03-11 00:22:39','2012-03-11 00:22:39','','Interview Custom Fields','','inherit','open','open','','acf_interview-custom-fields-15','','','2012-03-11 00:22:39','2012-03-11 00:22:39','',31,'http://spiraldesign.ca/acf_interview-custom-fields-15/',0,'revision','',0),(135,1,'2012-03-11 00:24:33','2012-03-11 00:24:33','','Arian Foster','','trash','closed','closed','','arian-foster','','','2012-03-25 21:26:21','2012-03-26 04:26:21','',0,'http://spiraldesign.ca/?post_type=interview&#038;p=135',0,'interview','',0),(136,1,'2012-03-11 00:26:06','2012-03-11 00:26:06','','Chuck Anderson','','publish','closed','closed','','chuck-anderso','','','2012-03-25 21:25:20','2012-03-26 04:25:20','',0,'http://spiraldesign.ca/?post_type=interview&#038;p=136',0,'interview','',0),(137,1,'2012-03-11 00:26:43','2012-03-11 00:26:43','','Jordan Swerdloff ','','publish','closed','closed','','jordanordan-swerdloff','','','2012-03-25 21:37:55','2012-03-26 04:37:55','',0,'http://spiraldesign.ca/?post_type=interview&#038;p=137',0,'interview','',0),(138,1,'2012-03-11 00:32:36','2012